<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>night man • night person</xh5><p> <i>night man—</i>1. a man who does work during the night: A company taxi is usually driven by both a day-man and a <u>nightman</u>. 2. a man who does illegal things at night: The people hated any type of investigator because so many of them were “<u>night men</u>.” 3. smb. who prefers to be active in the nighttime: Morris is a <u>night man</u>. He’d have a chapter from me morning or afternoon and then work on his at night.</p><p> <i>night person</i>— = night man 3: I can’t function in the morning. I’m strictly a <u>night person</u>.</p> </entry>
